citation.title: Eukleidou O̓ptika ̀kai katoptrikaʹ [romanized form] Euclidis Optica & catoptrica, nvnqvam antehac Græce ædita : eadem Latine reddita
citation.summary: Compilation of scientific texts; see printed catalogue for full description. The first text has been identified as a Latin translation of Theon of Alexandria's recension of Euclid's Optica; see Manuscripta vol. 21, 1977, p. 170-172. The third text comprises the translation of Muḥammad ibn Mūsá Khuwārizmī's Jabr wa-al-muqābalah by Gherard of Cremona, given the Latin title "Liber algebre et almuchabala." For the critical edition see Mediaeval Studies vol. 48, 1986, p. 233-263.
